cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of resource allocation in device-to-device (D2D) communication, which is a subfield of wireless networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a machine learning approach to predict D2D channel gains from cellular channel measurements, which involves statistical modeling and prediction, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The use of machine learning also suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible category. The paper also deals with radio resource management, which involves control and optimization of network resources, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of deep learning for prediction, which involves image and signal processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category.
